The paper discusses a method to construct a possibilistic logic theory that captures what can be derived from a given Markov logic network (MLN) using maximum a posteriori (MAP) inference. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), natural language processing (cs.CL), cryptography and security (cs.CR), or social and information networks (cs.SI).
